main event: A civilian reported seeing a round or saucer-like object hovering in the sky over Rochester, New York on March 12, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed by multiple witnesses, including at a recording station.
Two F-101 jet interceptors were launched to investigate, but the object had already disappeared.
The object was described as being 2-3 feet in diameter and hovering, with no visible means of propulsion.
The report includes a letter requesting information and pamphlets about unidentified flying objects and related phenomena.
witnesses: civilian, multiple observers at a recording station
